<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I recently started having an issue where if I try to use <code>package-refresh-contents</code> or <code>package-vc-install</code> that emacs will hang with the message <code>Contacting host:</code> <a href="https://elpa.gnu.org:443"><code>elpa.gnu.org:443</code></a> for a while (~2-3 minutes). If it stops hanging after this point, it will then hang on <code>package frefresh done</code> (for 3-4 minutes). I did not change anything related to this in my configuration prior to this issue starting. This also happens w/ <code>emacs -Q</code> and a test configuration. I have tried adding <code>(custom-set-variables &#39;(gnutls-algorithm-priority &quot;normal:-vers-tls1.3&quot;))</code> based on <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/a/60638601">this forum post</a> but the issue persists. Any help is appreciated.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/Far-Anywhere2876"> /u/Far-Anywhere2876 </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/13333hu/packagerefreshcontents_hangs_at_contacting_host/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/13333hu/packagerefreshcontents_hangs_at_contacting_host/">[comments]</a></span>